Codility challenge Minum Banners: 
Find a solution that takes an array and <br>
returns size of 2 banners that will cover <br>
all the buildings <br> 

Solution:
def solution(H):
    N = len(H)
    maxFromLeft = [0]*(N+1)
    maxFromRight = [0]*(N+1)

    cur_max = 0
    for i in range(N):
        cur_max = max(cur_max, H[i])
        maxFromLeft[i+1] = cur_max
    cur_max = 0
    for i in range(N-1, -1, -1):
        cur_max = max(cur_max, H[i])
        maxFromRight[i] = cur_max

    result = float("inf")
    for i in range(N+1):
        result = min(result, maxFromLeft[i]*i + maxFromRight[i]*(N-i))
    return result
